Q15 [SENIOR] | Design
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
QUESTION:
  Compare embedding vs inheritance in Go. What are the tradeoffs?

ANSWER:
  Go has NO inheritance. It achieves code reuse through composition
  via struct embedding.

  How embedding works:
    type Animal struct {
        Name string
    }
    func (a Animal) Speak() string { return a.Name + " speaks" }

    type Dog struct {
        Animal          // embedded — promotes Animal's methods
        Breed string
    }

    d := Dog{Animal: Animal{Name: "Rex"}, Breed: "Lab"}
    fmt.Println(d.Speak())  // promoted — works without d.Animal.Speak()

  Key differences from inheritance:
  ┌─────────────────────────┬────────────────────────┬──────────────────────┐
  │ Aspect                  │ OOP Inheritance        │ Go Embedding         │
  ├─────────────────────────┼────────────────────────┼──────────────────────┤
  │ Method override         │ Polymorphic dispatch   │ Shadowing only       │
  │ "is-a" relationship     │ Enforced by language   │ Not implied          │
  │ Interface satisfaction  │ Inherited              │ Promoted methods     │
  │ Hierarchy depth         │ Can be deep            │ Stays shallow        │
  │ Coupling                │ Tight (parent/child)   │ Loose (composition)  │
  └─────────────────────────┴────────────────────────┴──────────────────────┘

  Tradeoffs:
    - Promoted methods use the embedded type's receiver — if Dog shadows
      Speak(), calling via Animal interface still calls Animal.Speak()
    - No runtime polymorphism — use interfaces for that
    - Multiple embedding can create ambiguity if both types have same method

  Prefer explicit delegation when behaviour needs true customisation:
    type Dog struct {
        animal Animal
    }
    func (d Dog) Speak() string { return "Woof" }  // full control

  Java comparison:
    Java class inheritance ≈ NOT possible in Go.
    Java composition pattern (wrapping) ≈ Go explicit delegation.
    Java interface default methods ≈ Go interface embedding (partial).

